Implemented S03 in [model_call_service.rs](/Users/will/dev/nunchi/roko/roko/.roko/worktrees/converge-run-20260428-045041/crates/roko-agent/src/model_call_service.rs:21).

What changed:
- Added a closure-based CascadeRouter hook to avoid the `roko-agent` -> `roko-learn` dependency cycle.
- Added `with_cascade_router(...)`.
- Updated `resolve_model` to use the router when `req.model` is empty, passing `req.role.as_deref()`.
- Removed the old `TODO(arch)` comment.
- Added `cascade_router_selects_model_when_request_is_empty`.

Verification passed:
- `cargo check -p roko-agent`
- `grep -q 'with_cascade_router' crates/roko-agent/src/model_call_service.rs`
- `! grep -q 'TODO(arch): Route through CascadeRouter' crates/roko-agent/src/model_call_service.rs`
- `cargo test -p roko-agent model_call_service`
- `cargo test -p roko-agent cascade_router_selects_model`

`Cargo.toml` was not changed because `roko-learn` already depends on `roko-agent`, so a normal dependency would create a cycle.
